---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Methodology — CompoundVR" description="How CompoundVR evaluates flat-to-VR games and mods.">
  <section class="container section">
    <div class="eyebrow">Methodology</div>
    <h1>We review flat-to-VR routes like decisions, not hype cycles.</h1>
    <p class="lead">CompoundVR is built to answer whether a VR route is worth your time, not just whether it technically exists.</p>

    <div class="grid two" style="margin-top:2rem;">
      <div class="card"><h2>What we score</h2><p class="lead" style="font-size:1rem;max-width:none;">Playability, setup burden, input quality, comfort, performance, and support status.</p></div>
      <div class="card"><h2>What we avoid</h2><p class="lead" style="font-size:1rem;max-width:none;">Low-value churn, untested hype, and pretending tinkerer-only builds are casual recommendations.</p></div>
    </div>

    <article class="prose" style="margin-top:2rem;">
      <h2>Editorial standard</h2>
      <p>Canonical game pages are the core unit of the site. News, setup guides, and comparison pages support those evergreen verdicts rather than replacing them.</p>
      <h2>Recommendation language</h2>
      <p>Readers should know quickly whether a route is broadly recommended, caveat-heavy, or only for enthusiasts willing to tinker.</p>
      <h2>Why this matters</h2>
      <p>Flat-to-VR players waste huge amounts of time on vague recommendations. CompoundVR exists to reduce that waste with clearer judgment and better structure.</p>
    </article>
  </section>
</Layout>
